{"ticker": "ABSI", "company": "ABSCI CORP", "weight_sum": 7.5200000000000005, "etfs": ["ARKG", "ARKUX", "ARKVX", "ARKSX"], "is_private": false, "query": "($ABSI OR \"Absci\") -is:retweet min_faves:10 since_time:1777675515 until_time:1777689523", "n_fetched": 1, "n_kept": 1, "n_dropped": 0, "kept": [{"type": "tweet", "id": "2050030378589601904", "url": "https://x.com/crypto_condom/status/2050030378589601904", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/crypto_condom/status/2050030378589601904", "text": "These $ABSI calls are now up 185% in 2 weeks. One thing that gave me conviction on the initial trade was looking at insider transactions. \n\nTwo wit, in regards to $ABSI, two of the buyers \u2014 Frans Van Houten (former Philips CEO) and Menelas Pangalos (former Executive VP of BioPharmaceuticals R&D at AstraZeneca) \u2014 are heavyweight outside directors with deep industry expertise and no compensation incentive to \"support the stock.\" \nPangalos increased his stake by 527% and Van Houten by 172% in open-market trades. \n\nLastly, the Chief Innovation Officer bought TWICE \u2014 and the second time, right before retiring. $ABSI  announced on March 3, 2026 that CIO Andreas Busch would retire March 31, 2026 and continue to co-chair Absci's Scientific Advisory Board. He nonetheless bought $229K of stock on March 12, 2026 \u2014 nine days into a publicly known retirement transition. Retiring executives typically liquidate, not accumulate. He'd already bought $152K back in July 2025.\n\nTLDR: Earnings are next week and insiders are buying into the ABS-201 interim readouts that now define the company's value. \ud83c\udf4c", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 0, "replyCount": 3, "likeCount": 40, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 6390, "createdAt": "Fri May 01 01:51:44 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 16, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2050030378589601904", "displayTextRange": [0, 272], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": n